text.tspan: Monthly confirmed cases of influenza A (unknown subtype),
Non-sentinel surveillance includes data from multiple sources, including outbreak investigation, universal testing, and
testing at the point of care. Only a fraction of potential cases of influenza are tested by labs to confirm whether they have
influenza and to identify their strain. The level of testing may vary between countries and over time.
Data source: FluNet by the World Health Organization (2023)
Note: This shows the number of cases that were confirmed to be influenza A virus, but their subtype was not confirmed.
